question.title: Will Palestinian local elections be held on April 25, 2026?
question.description:
Whether elections occur as scheduled is a high-signal indicator of political feasibility and administrative capacity. Candidate Sources: https://www.elections.ps/TabId/1083/ArtMID/9183/ArticleID/5150/The-CEC-Announces-the-Legal-Periods-Associated-with-the-Different-Stages-of-the-2026-Local-Elections.aspx.

question.resolution_criteria: This question resolves as “Yes” if the Central Elections Commission (CEC) reports that voting for local elections occurred on April 25, 2026. Resolve “No” if the CEC announces postponement, suspension, or cancellation such that voting does not occur on April 25, 2026. Primary source: CEC publications on the 2026 local elections process, including the CEC announcement page: https://www.elections.ps/TabId/1083/ArtMID/9183/ArticleID/5148/The-CEC-Receives-the-Cabinets-Decision-Announcing-the-Date-for-Commencing-Local-Elections.aspx.
question.fine_print: “Held” means election day voting occurs (not merely that a schedule exists). If voting occurs only in a limited subset of areas and the CEC states the elections were not held as a general local election on that date, resolve “No”. Question may also resolve using credible sources per https://www.metaculus.com/faq/#definitions.
